<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="189" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="189">
Genus 
<taxonomicName LSID="ED84DC85-289C-5555-BCCA-F4E499D1D1A3" authority="Chamberlin, 1922" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1922" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplodrassus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Haplodrassus Chamberlin, 1922</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="189" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="189">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="189">
This genus includes 83 species, mainly distributed in the Palaearctic (WSC 2022). A smaller number of species are known from the Nearctic and Oriental realms (WSC 2022). The genus was divided into nine species groups, based on morphological characteristics, by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.15298/arthsel.21.4.04" author="Omelko, MM" journalOrPublisher="Arthropoda Selecta" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" pagination="339 - 348" refId="B19" refString="Omelko, MM, Marusik, YM, 2012. A review of the Haplodrassus montanus -group (Aranei: Gnaphosidae) in the east Palearctic and preliminary grouping of the genus. Arthropoda Selecta 21 (4): 339 - 348, DOI: https://doi.org/10.15298/arthsel.21.4.04" title="A review of the Haplodrassus montanus - group (Aranei: Gnaphosidae) in the east Palearctic and preliminary grouping of the genus." url="https://doi.org/10.15298/arthsel.21.4.04" volume="21" year="2012">Omelko and Marusik (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, i.e., the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">caspius</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">dalmatensis</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">kulczynskii</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">mediterraneus</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Yan &amp; Xiao &amp; Luo &amp; Xiao &amp; Fomichev" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplodrassus montanus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">Haplodrassus montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">signifier</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">silvestris</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">tegulatus</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">umbratilis</emphasis>
groups. To date, only 13 species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1922" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplodrassus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">Haplodrassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are recorded from China. Except for 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Haplodrassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplodrassus guiyangensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guiyangensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">Haplodrassus guiyangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Yan &amp; Yu, 2021, the others were recorded more than 10 years ago.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
